    • findTimeZone

      private java.util.TimeZone findTimeZone​(java.lang.String q)
      Finds the corresponding TimeZone object to the provided string.

      Warning: this method may be expensive to run.

      The provided string should be representative of a time zone in either IANA format or its canonical aliases. If a time zone cannot be found, then DEFAULT_TZ is returned.

      Parameters:
      q - The alias to lookup.
      Returns:
      The TimeZone object corresponding to the alias.

    • getChatTimestamp

      public java.lang.String getChatTimestamp()
      Generates a timestamp.

      For example, "2021/02/27 06:23:15 [0726 ms] PM PST".

      Returns:
      The timestamp in question in the format specified in the sample output.
